1
00:00:20,720 --> 00:00:25,320
♪ I have a heart and know how to love ♪

2
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:29,880
♪ Especially when I see you
I keep seeing the scenes ♪

3
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:33,320
♪ From when we were together ♪

4
00:00:33,320 --> 00:00:36,520
♪ But I keep seeing you in my head ♪

5
00:00:36,760 --> 00:00:41,240
♪ My broken heart hasn't recovered ♪

6
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:43,840
♪ So I hurt you ♪

7
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:49,160
♪ Even though I have to
Make myself watch you cry ♪

8
00:00:50,840 --> 00:00:55,440
♪ I hate it but I still do it ♪

9
00:00:55,440 --> 00:00:59,400
♪ I keep picking at scabs to hurt you ♪

10
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:06,960
♪ I want to escape
But it feels like walking in circles ♪

11
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:11,680
♪ In the end I hurt myself
Keeping my love hidden ♪

12
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:14,920
♪ I can't walk away even if I want to ♪

13
00:01:14,920 --> 00:01:19,960
♪ My love must be hidden
I can hardly stand it ♪

14
00:01:19,960 --> 00:01:22,840
♪ It's torture when you cry ♪

15
00:01:22,920 --> 00:01:26,720
♪ The more you're hurt ♪

16
00:01:26,880 --> 00:01:30,840
♪ The weaker my heart becomes ♪

17
00:01:31,440 --> 00:01:37,320
♪ I try not to love you
Holding back my tears while saying goodbye ♪

18
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:41,520
♪ But I could never do it for real ♪

19
00:01:42,960 --> 00:01:44,080
Missing that brat?

20
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:46,720
Even since you ran into that brat,
you've been moody.

21
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:48,000
I hate feeling like this.

22
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,320
Do you want it to stop?

23
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:50,440
You know how?

24
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:53,160
Yes, but you have to cooperate.

25
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:58,400
-I know you hate me.
-Yes, I despise you.

26
00:01:58,400 --> 00:01:59,520
Earn, watch out!

27
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:01,800
I still love you.

28
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:04,960
Love? You dare use the word "love"?

29
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:07,840
I do. I love you.

30
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:10,479
And I'll do everything
to make you love me again.

31
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:12,600
There's no "again" between us.

32
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:15,600
YOU'LL LIKE IT

33
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:17,160
Hey, this one's delicious.

34
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:22,200
You're right.

35
00:02:22,640 --> 00:02:23,640
Lada.

36
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:26,120
Here. Enjoying the food?

37
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:30,680
She's not enjoying it.

38
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:35,800
Jealous, aren't you?
That's why you're taking it out on your friends.

39
00:02:36,440 --> 00:02:37,440
Who's jealous?

40
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:40,680
Duh. Aren't you aware at all?

41
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:44,080
Even since you saw your ex
walking with that actress,

42
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,640
you've been so obvious.

43
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:48,040
You're wrong.

44
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:50,920
Fine. Whatever you say.

45
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:53,560
You can lie to us all you want.

46
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:55,160
but you can't lie to yourself.

47
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:57,800
Because you're being super obvious.

48
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,560
Hey, come on.

49
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:03,640
You don't have to say everything you know.

50
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,120
Lada's well aware.

51
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:07,200
I'm not bothered.

52
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:10,960
It's her business who she hangs out with.
Why would it bother me?

53
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:12,400
Okay, okay, okay.

54
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,040
So you're not bothered.

55
00:03:14,040 --> 00:03:15,840
I'm the only bothered one here.

56
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:20,000
Look at us. We finally found the time
to hang out outside the hospital,

57
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:21,600
I didn't get my free omakase.

58
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:25,200
Hey, this is free too.

59
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:27,240
Because Lada's treating us.

60
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:29,200
Oh, then let's eat.

61
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:30,920
I'm happy now.

62
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:35,800
Come to mama.

63
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:36,960
This looks so good.

64
00:03:37,040 --> 00:03:39,240
Enjoy this free food. I'm enjoying it.

65
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,240
Please do.

66
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:07,440
You're drenched.

67
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,120
Huh?

68
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:10,560
You're drenched.

69
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:28,440
This is so cute.

70
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,560
Thank you, Engfah.

71
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:34,960
I'll do it myself.

72
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:36,800
Sure.

73
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,960
-Engfah?
-Hm?

74
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:16,640
Can I ask you something honestly?

75
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:22,840
What's up? Why are you being so serious?

76
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:25,680
Let me ask you honestly.

77
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:30,160
You like women, right?

78
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:43,360
Why are you asking me that?

79
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:47,040
I'm just curious.

80
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:51,320
Yes.

81
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:53,880
I like women.

82
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:01,880
Got it.

83
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:06,560
Hold on.

84
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:08,840
I'm not finished.

85
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:11,200
Yes?

86
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:22,840
If you're the woman I'm into,

87
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:26,200
what would you say?

88
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:41,160
Lada. You're okay.

89
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:42,920
You're okay.

90
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:45,760
You're okay, I'm okay, me okay, okay?

91
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:47,600
Okay.

92
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:55,400
Doctor, your first patient's here.

93
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:56,480
Please let them in.

94
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:00,880
Hello, Doc.

95
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:06,320
Not okay.

96
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:08,880
What did you say?

97
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:15,880
Please leave, Ms. Rose.

98
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:19,160
I'll take care of this one myself.

99
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,280
I see.

100
00:08:20,880 --> 00:08:21,960
Got it, Doctor.

101
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:45,640
I got you banoffee pies.

102
00:08:56,880 --> 00:08:58,240
Dang, I can't hear anything.

103
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:01,640
I have to get Doctors Bow and Tan.

104
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:23,520
You don't like banoffee pies anymore?

105
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:25,800
I stopped liking it two years ago.

106
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:29,240
Please leave.

107
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:36,360
I know you don't want to see me.

108
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:39,960
But I still want to see you every day.

109
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,560
That's your problem.

110
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:46,080
And my problem is to figure out
how to get you out of my life.

111
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:47,600
No, I won't get out...

112
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:49,600
I have someone I love now.

113
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:54,600
And I'm going to marry him soon.

114
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:00,440
The person you're talking about...

115
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:03,320
Is he Dr. Wisanu?

116
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:06,120
How did you know?

117
00:10:06,680 --> 00:10:09,840
I happened to watch TV the other day.

118
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:11,840
And I saw his interview.

119
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:14,320
But from what I heard...

120
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:19,960
you're not into him.

121
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:24,760
He's still trying to win you.

122
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:36,960
Do I need to kiss him...

123
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:39,760
for you to believe me?

124
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,200
Do it.

125
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:47,120
I want to know too

126
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:49,480
if you can kiss a man.

127
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:05,240
WISANU

128
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:07,760
I think you'll get more than a kiss.

129
00:11:13,920 --> 00:11:15,320
Hello, Nu.

130
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:18,360
I was just thinking about you.

131
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:26,480
What's that?

132
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,760
You're coming to see me?

133
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:30,040
Of course you can.

134
00:11:30,560 --> 00:11:31,880
Hurry.

135
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:33,600
I missed you.

136
00:12:13,360 --> 00:12:15,200
PLASTIC AND SURGERY DEPARTMENT

137
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,680
Hello, Nu.

138
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,600
Oh, just now?

139
00:13:02,560 --> 00:13:04,640
No, I didn't say that.

140
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:07,360
You probably heard it wrong.

141
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:08,880
I said...

142
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:10,840
I missed Taohu.

143
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,280
I want to play with him.

144
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:19,440
Okay.

145
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,000
Yes.

146
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:25,640
Dr. Fahlada, you have
a 001 case on the second floor.

147
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:30,720
I repeat. Dr. Fahlada,
you have a 001 case on the second floor.

148
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:34,080
Nu, I have an urgent case.

149
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:36,880
I don't think I can see you today.
I have to go.

150
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:41,120
Lada,

151
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:42,440
did you go overboard?

152
00:13:42,520 --> 00:13:44,800
She looked like she was crying.

153
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:46,160
You're exaggerating.

154
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:49,040
She wasn't crying. She just got teary eyes.

155
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:53,520
Emotional pain can't be
measured by the amount of tear.

156
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:58,120
I could tell from just her face
that she was in great pain.

157
00:13:59,680 --> 00:14:03,280
That was nothing compared to
what she did to me.

158
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:04,880
That's right.

159
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:07,160
You weren't there when that brat hurt Lada.

160
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:08,200
You wouldn't get it.

161
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,240
Fine.

162
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:12,160
I don't know.

163
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:15,080
We're all women.
I can't help empathizing with her.

164
00:14:15,760 --> 00:14:16,840
It can't be helped.

165
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:18,880
She chose to come to me.

166
00:14:23,560 --> 00:14:24,760
Hey, Lada.

167
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:26,640
Are you wavering?

168
00:14:27,520 --> 00:14:28,520
No.

169
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:31,520
Good. That's my girl.

170
00:14:32,840 --> 00:14:36,120
What if she gets so upset she hurt herself?

171
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:37,840
Did you think of that?

172
00:15:09,280 --> 00:15:10,360
No way.

173
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:14,040
She's too self-absorbed to ever hurt herself.

174
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:16,280
She would only hurt other people.

175
00:15:16,280 --> 00:15:17,480
Trust me.

176
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:19,720
-But I...
-Jeez, Bow.

177
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:21,480
Whose friend are you?

178
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:23,680
Why are you making her doubt?

179
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:25,280
She was about to get past it.

180
00:15:25,960 --> 00:15:26,960
Fine.

181
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:28,760
I was asking just in case.

182
00:15:28,960 --> 00:15:31,320
But if you two are sure, then never mind.

183
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:34,640
I hope she'll get over it soon.

184
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:39,960
Dr. Bow, the ER called to get you.

185
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:41,640
I sneaked out just for a bit.

186
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:44,080
A woman was hit by a car
in front of the hospital.

187
00:15:44,080 --> 00:15:45,080
Really?

188
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:49,400
Where are you going, Doctor?

189
00:15:50,040 --> 00:15:51,040
Come on.

190
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:56,760
Where's the patient who got hit by a car?

191
00:15:56,760 --> 00:15:58,000
Oh, this way, Doctor.

192
00:16:04,560 --> 00:16:05,600
Earn?

193
00:16:07,920 --> 00:16:08,920
Uh...

194
00:16:09,680 --> 00:16:10,680
Uh...

195
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:12,960
I'll dress your wounds.

196
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:15,120
Where are you hurt?

197
00:16:16,520 --> 00:16:17,800
Dr. Fahlada?

198
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:20,320
I'm an ER doctor.

199
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:22,640
You forgot I studied
emergency medicine, didn't you?

200
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:25,200
Yeah.

201
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:26,360
Please.

202
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:31,000
Dermatology's that way.

203
00:16:32,040 --> 00:16:33,560
-What are your symptoms?
-That's right.

204
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:40,040
I'm going to have to press it.

205
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:42,040
If anything hurts, let me know.

206
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:52,320
You were worried about her

207
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:55,240
but lied that you weren't.

208
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:57,920
You're an awful liar, Lada.

209
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,000
No.

210
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:00,960
I wasn't worried about her.

211
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:03,800
I was worried about
the patient who got hit by a car.

212
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:05,599
-Really?
-Really?

213
00:17:06,280 --> 00:17:08,640
I wouldn't believe you
even if you were the Buddha.

214
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:11,760
I assure you

215
00:17:11,839 --> 00:17:13,960
that person died to me a long time ago.

216
00:17:15,960 --> 00:17:17,440
What if...

217
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:20,960
she came back to life?

218
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:24,160
How can dead people come back to life?

219
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:25,800
-Ooh.
-Ooh.

220
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:27,200
-Harsh.
-Harsh.

221
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,000
Hey!

222
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:50,280
Miss? Miss, are you all right?

223
00:18:58,120 --> 00:19:01,160
Someone just went into shock in the ER.

224
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:03,320
This is a hospital.

225
00:19:03,320 --> 00:19:05,000
People go into shock almost every day.

226
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:06,160
What's so exciting?

227
00:19:06,360 --> 00:19:09,040
But this was Earn, the actress.

228
00:19:09,360 --> 00:19:11,480
She came to our ward this morning.

229
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:13,720
-Really?
-Yes.

230
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:18,600
Doctor.

231
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:21,880
Ple just told me someone
went into shock in the ER.

232
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:23,520
Leave other wards alone.

233
00:19:23,840 --> 00:19:25,240
Is my patient here yet?

234
00:19:25,680 --> 00:19:27,920
I don't want to meddle, Doctor.

235
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,720
But this person is Earn, Sanitada.

236
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:42,480
Please relax. The doctor's coming.

237
00:19:43,080 --> 00:19:44,280
Breathe slowly.

238
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:53,160
-What are the vital signs?
-BP is 90/50.

239
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:54,560
Pulse rate is 100 per minute.

240
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:55,960
SAT is 95 percent.

241
00:19:58,800 --> 00:20:02,600
Give her Ventolin
and free-flow normal saline.

242
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:08,840
The patient has a banana anaphylaxis, Doctor.

243
00:20:08,880 --> 00:20:10,480
I suspect the same thing here.

244
00:20:10,480 --> 00:20:12,760
Are you related to the patient, Doctor?

245
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:15,920
Yes.

246
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:18,960
Uh, I saw she was eating a banana.

247
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:21,000
It's probably like what Dr. Lada said.

248
00:20:21,040 --> 00:20:23,560
Then give her adrenaline at 1/1000.

249
00:20:23,560 --> 00:20:25,280
0.5 ml IM.

250
00:20:25,280 --> 00:20:29,440
CPM 1 amp IV. Dexa 5 mg IV. And...

251
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:00,440
Doc?

252
00:21:06,480 --> 00:21:07,520
How are you feeling?

253
00:21:09,920 --> 00:21:11,440
I'm fine.

254
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:13,360
I'm so glad

255
00:21:13,920 --> 00:21:16,240
you're the first person I woke up to.

256
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:18,600
Is this a happy matter?

257
00:21:19,360 --> 00:21:20,640
You did something stupid.

258
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:22,280
Did you have a death wish?

259
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:26,800
Doc, you're misunderstanding me.

260
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,120
How's that?

261
00:21:28,920 --> 00:21:31,520
You ate a banana
when you knew you were allergic.

262
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:33,240
What was that if not a death wish?

263
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:39,360
I just wanted to know...

264
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:42,720
if you would care about me.

265
00:21:44,360 --> 00:21:46,640
If that's the case, you're being selfish.

266
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:50,400
Didn't you realize
the ER was for urgent care?

267
00:21:50,560 --> 00:21:53,640
There were sick people
who needed nurses and doctors.

268
00:21:54,080 --> 00:21:55,760
But you hurt yourself

269
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:57,840
to get attention?

270
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:02,960
Learn to think of other people.

271
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:06,640
Don't just think about yourself.

272
00:22:13,280 --> 00:22:14,360
You're right.

273
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:16,440
I'm being selfish.

274
00:22:18,080 --> 00:22:21,760
But I did it because
I was afraid I'd lose you to...

275
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:30,280
To Dr. Wisanu.

276
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:34,760
Listen to me, Earn.

277
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:40,320
You lost me a long time ago.

278
00:22:40,680 --> 00:22:45,160
♪ My broken heart hasn't recovered ♪

279
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:47,680
♪ So I hurt you ♪

280
00:22:47,680 --> 00:22:52,920
♪ Even though I have to
Make myself watch you cry ♪

281
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:59,280
♪ I hate it but I still do it ♪

282
00:22:59,280 --> 00:23:03,240
♪ I keep picking at scabs to hurt you ♪

283
00:23:03,240 --> 00:23:10,800
♪ I want to escape
But it feels like walking in circles ♪

284
00:23:11,160 --> 00:23:15,520
♪ In the end I hurt myself
Keeping my love hidden ♪

285
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:18,720
♪ I can't walk away even if I want to ♪

286
00:23:18,720 --> 00:23:23,440
♪ My love must be hidden
I can hardly stand it ♪

287
00:23:23,600 --> 00:23:26,240
I don't like women! I like men!

288
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:28,600
I like man!

289
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:30,440
Do you get it now?

290
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:32,160
Earn!

291
00:23:32,480 --> 00:23:33,480
Earn!

292
00:23:33,720 --> 00:23:35,760
Earn! Earn! Earn! Don't leave!

293
00:23:35,960 --> 00:23:37,160
Earn!

294
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:41,240
♪ Holding back my tears while saying goodbye ♪

295
00:23:41,240 --> 00:23:45,520
♪ But I could never do it for real ♪

296
00:23:48,440 --> 00:23:51,760
She's gone. She left me.

297
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:54,800
You're just a toy I've grown tired of.
Just let me go.

298
00:23:55,040 --> 00:23:58,160
Please don't leave me, Tan.

299
00:23:58,680 --> 00:24:00,960
I've been fooling you.

300
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:03,840
Because I knew you were rich.
I just wanted a comfortable life.

301
00:24:03,880 --> 00:24:06,760
From this day on,
let's not see each other again.

302
00:24:06,760 --> 00:24:10,720
♪ The more you're hurt ♪

303
00:24:10,720 --> 00:24:12,720
♪ The weaker my heart becomes ♪

304
00:24:12,720 --> 00:24:15,000
Lada, calm down.

305
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:17,280
Calm down.

306
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:19,920
Breathe.

307
00:24:20,720 --> 00:24:22,040
Breathe.

308
00:24:22,120 --> 00:24:25,440
♪ But I could never do it for real ♪

309
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:31,880
Something wrong, Doctor?

310
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:37,280
No.

311
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:39,000
Do you need something?

312
00:24:40,800 --> 00:24:42,080
Your patient's here.

313
00:24:44,320 --> 00:24:45,520
Please let them in.

314
00:24:54,880 --> 00:24:55,880
Okay.

315
00:25:07,040 --> 00:25:08,280
Suzie.

316
00:25:14,320 --> 00:25:15,640
Here, take them.

317
00:25:18,040 --> 00:25:19,440
You having difficulty sleeping

318
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:22,280
is the only reason
I drove back to get your old plushies.

319
00:25:29,160 --> 00:25:30,720
-Thank you.
-Enough!

320
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:32,480
Leave your thanks there.

321
00:25:32,960 --> 00:25:34,880
Don't you dare thank me.

322
00:25:35,640 --> 00:25:37,640
Because I'm so mad at you.

323
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:39,200
Why?

324
00:25:39,560 --> 00:25:41,840
You're allergic to banana
and you still ate it.

325
00:25:42,880 --> 00:25:43,920
Look at yourself.

326
00:25:43,920 --> 00:25:46,160
What if you don't recover
in time for the shoot?

327
00:25:46,160 --> 00:25:49,240
You knew you had responsibilities.

328
00:25:49,520 --> 00:25:52,640
A hundred of crew members
work to support their families.

329
00:25:53,280 --> 00:25:55,600
You're wasting their time
because you hurt yourself.

330
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:56,920
Is that right?

331
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:01,680
I'm sorry.

332
00:26:02,400 --> 00:26:03,400
Jeez.

333
00:26:04,600 --> 00:26:06,360
I'm glad you've learned your lesson.

334
00:26:06,360 --> 00:26:09,560
If you do this again, I won't talk to you.

335
00:26:09,560 --> 00:26:10,680
Remember that.

336
00:26:22,320 --> 00:26:23,320
Jeez.

337
00:26:24,680 --> 00:26:26,480
All right, I'll stop scolding you.

338
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:27,880
All right.

339
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:31,040
Jeez.

340
00:26:31,040 --> 00:26:32,400
I'll stop scolding you.

341
00:26:33,160 --> 00:26:35,440
Your eyes will get puffy
and we'll have to fix them.

342
00:26:52,280 --> 00:26:54,040
You're right for being angry.

343
00:26:54,200 --> 00:26:56,600
What a stupid thing to do for an adult.

344
00:26:56,600 --> 00:26:57,880
She was lucky to be alive.

345
00:26:59,640 --> 00:27:02,680
I think she ran out of ideas to win you back

346
00:27:02,720 --> 00:27:04,040
so she made that choice.

347
00:27:06,240 --> 00:27:08,920
She knew I'd never go back to her.

348
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:10,560
She should've left me alone.

349
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:13,120
Instead, she kept pestering me.

350
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:14,440
It's annoying.

351
00:27:17,040 --> 00:27:18,400
Let's just eat.

352
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:40,480
Here, have some orange.

353
00:27:41,120 --> 00:27:43,080
Orange. Not banana.

354
00:27:45,560 --> 00:27:46,560
Hey.

355
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:49,360
How long are you going to make a sour face?

356
00:27:49,360 --> 00:27:50,960
It's upsetting seeing you like this.

357
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:26,520
What are they talking about?

358
00:28:28,920 --> 00:28:30,800
I never wanted to get involved,

359
00:28:32,800 --> 00:28:34,560
but as Lada's close friend,

360
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:36,720
I really can't let this go.

361
00:28:39,600 --> 00:28:41,360
Can you do me a favor?

362
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:44,800
Will you leave my friend alone?

363
00:28:51,040 --> 00:28:53,360
Doc asked you to tell me, didn't she?

364
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:54,760
No, she didn't.

365
00:28:56,840 --> 00:28:58,320
But I feel for her.

366
00:29:00,400 --> 00:29:02,200
You've hurt her enough.

367
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:05,280
But I didn't mean to.

368
00:29:05,760 --> 00:29:07,280
I was hurt too.

369
00:29:07,440 --> 00:29:08,880
But not as much as she was.

370
00:29:11,800 --> 00:29:14,280
Have you any idea the day you left her,

371
00:29:15,240 --> 00:29:16,720
her life was a living hell?

372
00:29:19,680 --> 00:29:21,400
She walled off everything.

373
00:29:22,320 --> 00:29:23,760
She abandoned everything.

374
00:29:26,960 --> 00:29:28,120
Her future.

375
00:29:29,560 --> 00:29:30,760
Her education.

376
00:29:32,840 --> 00:29:34,120
Even her family.

377
00:29:35,760 --> 00:29:37,920
My friend's life was ruined once.

378
00:29:40,480 --> 00:29:42,240
Please don't ruin it again.

379
00:29:47,920 --> 00:29:49,000
Doc...

380
00:29:51,240 --> 00:29:53,320
was really that hurt?

381
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:56,040
Yes.

382
00:29:58,640 --> 00:30:01,200
She was hurt in the way you couldn't imagine,

383
00:30:02,520 --> 00:30:03,520
Ms. Earn.

384
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:07,440
Hello, girl.

385
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:10,520
Come on,
I'm planning on shopping before class.

386
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:16,680
Lada?

387
00:30:19,760 --> 00:30:20,880
Why are you crying?

388
00:30:20,960 --> 00:30:22,160
Tan.

389
00:30:22,240 --> 00:30:23,240
What's wrong?

390
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:25,960
Earn left me.

391
00:30:26,120 --> 00:30:27,120
Huh?

392
00:30:27,360 --> 00:30:28,360
Why?

393
00:30:29,640 --> 00:30:33,120
She's gone. She left me.

394
00:30:36,720 --> 00:30:38,800
Calm down. Calm down.

395
00:30:39,920 --> 00:30:43,640
-It's because I'm not a man, isn't it?
-Calm down, Lada.

396
00:30:43,640 --> 00:30:45,240
-So she left me.
-Lada.

397
00:30:45,800 --> 00:30:47,000
-Lada.
-Why...

398
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:49,440
Lada, calm down. Calm down.

399
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:52,440
Lada.

400
00:30:54,080 --> 00:30:56,000
Here, take it.

401
00:30:57,120 --> 00:30:58,120
What's that?

402
00:30:59,120 --> 00:31:00,280
Lecture notes.

403
00:31:00,520 --> 00:31:02,240
I went to your classes for you.

404
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:05,440
At this rate, I'll be a dermatologist
instead of a surgeon.

405
00:31:07,960 --> 00:31:08,960
Great.

406
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:12,440
Lada, when will you stop acting like this?

407
00:31:12,800 --> 00:31:14,200
This is so not you.

408
00:31:14,440 --> 00:31:15,840
What am I usually like?

409
00:31:15,840 --> 00:31:17,680
More human than this.

410
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:21,680
I'm still a human.

411
00:31:21,760 --> 00:31:23,040
A good human too.

412
00:31:23,040 --> 00:31:24,760
Enough, stop drinking, Lada.

413
00:31:24,760 --> 00:31:25,760
Let go.

414
00:31:26,080 --> 00:31:27,200
Stop drinking.

415
00:31:27,600 --> 00:31:29,160
-Give it!
-No!

416
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:31,400
-Lada, you've been drinking... No!
-Give it!

417
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:32,400
Lada, stop!

418
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:34,440
-You won't give it back?
-Stop!

419
00:31:34,480 --> 00:31:37,040
Stop! Lada, enough. Enough. That's enough.

420
00:31:37,120 --> 00:31:38,960
-Give it to me.
-Give it back!

421
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:40,880
-You want it?
-Tan...

422
00:31:45,280 --> 00:31:48,440
Jeez. You're drunk every day.
This won't do.

423
00:31:50,480 --> 00:31:51,600
You stink.

424
00:31:52,040 --> 00:31:54,000
-Stink of what?
-Stink of booze. What else?

425
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:55,160
I disgust you?

426
00:31:55,720 --> 00:31:56,720
Oh!

427
00:31:56,760 --> 00:31:59,320
Oh! Lada!

428
00:31:59,640 --> 00:32:00,640
Jeez.

429
00:32:01,200 --> 00:32:02,200
Come here.

430
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:10,440
Don't breathe on me. It stinks.

431
00:32:10,440 --> 00:32:12,520
Hey, hey, hey!
Lada, are you going to barf?

432
00:32:18,680 --> 00:32:19,840
Enough, girl.

433
00:32:20,080 --> 00:32:21,240
That's enough.

434
00:32:22,360 --> 00:32:23,880
Let go, Lada.

435
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:26,480
Here.

436
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:29,840
Lecture notes.

437
00:32:31,120 --> 00:32:34,560
I go to so many of your classes
I'm about to graduate with you.

438
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:35,880
Lada.

439
00:32:36,360 --> 00:32:38,120
When will you get back up?

440
00:32:38,520 --> 00:32:40,200
You can't let yourself go like this.

441
00:32:44,960 --> 00:32:46,560
Stop crying and...

442
00:32:48,280 --> 00:32:49,960
Will you please stop crying?

443
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:51,880
Lada cried to me...

444
00:32:53,320 --> 00:32:54,880
over you all the time

445
00:32:56,200 --> 00:32:58,800
because she didn't know
the real reason you left.

446
00:33:00,280 --> 00:33:02,760
I love her.

447
00:33:06,960 --> 00:33:09,160
Why are you hurting my friend again?

448
00:33:14,640 --> 00:33:16,560
Her life was getting better.

449
00:33:20,520 --> 00:33:21,920
Please let my friend go.

450
00:33:22,880 --> 00:33:24,920
What you're doing right now...

451
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:29,280
is like you're hurting
a patient who's almost healed.

452
00:33:31,160 --> 00:33:32,440
Let me remind you.

453
00:33:33,080 --> 00:33:35,400
If a patient who's almost healed...

454
00:33:36,880 --> 00:33:39,560
gets seriously hurt again,

455
00:33:40,720 --> 00:33:42,920
they might succumb to their wounds...

456
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:46,120
and end up dead for real.

457
00:33:47,080 --> 00:33:50,160
But I didn't mean to.
I did what I did because...

458
00:33:50,160 --> 00:33:51,920
The reason doesn't matter anymore.

459
00:33:54,600 --> 00:33:56,360
I see what you're doing.

460
00:33:56,760 --> 00:33:58,800
The way you're harassing her,

461
00:33:58,800 --> 00:34:00,200
it makes her uncomfortable.

462
00:34:02,360 --> 00:34:05,800
Lada's been kind to you
for not hurting you more.

463
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:07,840
Because if I were her,

464
00:34:09,080 --> 00:34:11,800
you would've never stepped inside this hospital.

465
00:36:30,720 --> 00:36:31,840
Stubborn girl.

466
00:36:33,480 --> 00:36:35,400
You always worry me.

467
00:37:49,120 --> 00:37:50,120
Doctor?

468
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:53,080
Dr. Fahlada?

469
00:38:11,280 --> 00:38:12,280
Wrong room.

470
00:38:20,440 --> 00:38:22,200
What's with her?

471
00:40:13,760 --> 00:40:15,840
You lost me a long time ago.

472
00:40:56,840 --> 00:40:58,920
Will you leave my friend alone?

473
00:40:59,320 --> 00:41:01,680
Have you any idea the day you left her,

474
00:41:02,720 --> 00:41:04,120
her life was a living hell?

475
00:41:04,520 --> 00:41:06,440
Her life was getting better.

476
00:41:10,160 --> 00:41:12,080
Please let my friend go.

477
00:41:16,360 --> 00:41:18,880
What if I ask you for one last chance?

478
00:41:20,120 --> 00:41:22,680
I promise it won't end like last time.

479
00:41:24,520 --> 00:41:28,000
This time I'm going to make her
a completely healed patient.

480
00:41:29,680 --> 00:41:31,760
I'm going to heal her heart myself.

481
00:41:43,280 --> 00:41:45,320
New skirt. Isn't it pretty?

482
00:41:46,320 --> 00:41:47,480
Watch me.

483
00:41:48,240 --> 00:41:50,480
What's this, Suzie? Let me see.

484
00:41:50,480 --> 00:41:51,840
It's fabulous, auntie.

485
00:41:51,840 --> 00:41:53,920
-Pack up.
-Fold it.

486
00:41:59,160 --> 00:42:00,960
How are you feeling, sick girl?

487
00:42:02,280 --> 00:42:03,440
Engfah?

488
00:42:03,720 --> 00:42:04,960
How did you get here?

489
00:42:06,840 --> 00:42:08,920
Suzie texted me via LINE last night

490
00:42:08,920 --> 00:42:11,440
that you were sick and admitted here.

491
00:42:11,440 --> 00:42:13,040
So I came by to visit.

492
00:42:14,880 --> 00:42:16,440
I'm fine now.

493
00:42:16,480 --> 00:42:18,240
I was released me this morning.

494
00:42:18,800 --> 00:42:22,280
I'm glad I made it in time
or I would've found someone else here.

495
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:25,600
You're so sweet, Eng,

496
00:42:25,600 --> 00:42:28,160
for taking your precious time to visit Earn.

497
00:42:28,400 --> 00:42:30,720
So let's leave, shall we?

498
00:42:31,400 --> 00:42:32,400
I need sleep.

499
00:42:35,960 --> 00:42:37,560
-Let's go.
-Give them here.

500
00:42:37,560 --> 00:42:38,680
-Huh?
-I'll carry them.

501
00:42:38,680 --> 00:42:39,680
-Everything?
-Yes.

502
00:42:42,640 --> 00:42:43,640
Come on.

503
00:42:44,560 --> 00:42:46,560
I'll help you with this one.

504
00:42:47,560 --> 00:42:49,040
Come on, I'll help.

505
00:42:53,840 --> 00:42:55,520
-Thank you.
-Let's go.

506
00:42:57,360 --> 00:42:59,120
-Can you manage?
-Yes, piece of cake.

507
00:43:29,000 --> 00:43:30,000
Oh!

508
00:43:30,520 --> 00:43:32,360
Dr. Fahlada, hello.

509
00:43:33,000 --> 00:43:34,000
Hello.

510
00:43:34,760 --> 00:43:36,000
You're leaving?

511
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:38,960
Yes. Oh, thank you so much

512
00:43:39,120 --> 00:43:43,120
for arranging the room for Earn
before I got here

513
00:43:45,640 --> 00:43:47,480
The staff arranged it.

514
00:43:47,920 --> 00:43:49,000
I didn't do anything.

515
00:43:55,920 --> 00:43:57,000
Doc.

516
00:44:00,320 --> 00:44:01,320
I...

517
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:04,240
I'm leaving.

518
00:44:05,000 --> 00:44:06,080
Goodbye.

519
00:44:08,440 --> 00:44:10,000
I've heard a lot about you.

520
00:44:11,880 --> 00:44:13,320
I'm glad to finally meet you.

521
00:44:16,680 --> 00:44:19,520
Well, it'd be inappropriate
to say I hope to see you again.

522
00:44:21,040 --> 00:44:23,000
Since the reason we see a doctor

523
00:44:23,280 --> 00:44:24,680
is that we're sick, right?

524
00:44:25,200 --> 00:44:26,960
We can meet for other reasons.

525
00:44:30,520 --> 00:44:31,920
There won't be one.

526
00:44:40,840 --> 00:44:42,280
Who's calling?

527
00:44:42,280 --> 00:44:43,640
Is it a scammer?

528
00:44:46,000 --> 00:44:47,000
Hello?

529
00:44:47,520 --> 00:44:48,520
Oh!

530
00:44:50,480 --> 00:44:51,720
A duo gig?

531
00:44:52,040 --> 00:44:53,040
Wow.

532
00:44:53,880 --> 00:44:55,360
I'll call you right back.

533
00:44:58,440 --> 00:45:00,800
How has this video gotten so many views?

534
00:45:01,840 --> 00:45:03,160
-What video?
-Duh.

535
00:45:04,880 --> 00:45:06,800
The video of you two of course.

536
00:45:06,800 --> 00:45:09,840
I thought it was cute so I posted it on IG.

537
00:45:09,840 --> 00:45:11,240
It got so much attention.

538
00:45:17,000 --> 00:45:19,000
This is so cute.

539
00:45:19,640 --> 00:45:21,040
Ooh, just a sec.

540
00:45:21,360 --> 00:45:22,400
-Oh!
-Huh?

541
00:45:22,400 --> 00:45:23,680
"Earn's Eng."

542
00:45:25,080 --> 00:45:26,560
A new fandom.

543
00:45:26,720 --> 00:45:27,840
By the look of it,

544
00:45:28,040 --> 00:45:31,080
The two of you, Eng and Earn,

545
00:45:31,080 --> 00:45:33,560
will become a new imagined couple.

546
00:45:36,440 --> 00:45:37,960
Let me take this call.

547
00:45:40,760 --> 00:45:43,080
-Hello?
-Today we're an imagined couple,

548
00:45:44,040 --> 00:45:45,480
but in the future,

549
00:45:48,280 --> 00:45:50,360
we might become a real couple.

550
00:46:15,960 --> 00:46:20,320
♪ In the end I hurt myself
Keeping my love hidden ♪

551
00:46:20,360 --> 00:46:23,560
♪ I can't walk away even if I want to ♪

552
00:46:23,600 --> 00:46:28,600
♪ My love must be hidden
I can hardly stand it ♪

553
00:46:28,640 --> 00:46:31,520
♪ It's torture when you cry ♪

554
00:46:31,520 --> 00:46:35,520
♪ The more you're hurt ♪

555
00:46:35,520 --> 00:46:39,440
♪ The weaker my heart becomes ♪

556
00:46:39,720 --> 00:46:42,120
Hello, Engfah, where are you?

557
00:46:42,280 --> 00:46:43,760
What mood are you in, Doctor,

558
00:46:43,760 --> 00:46:46,040
that got you sit alone quietly here?

559
00:46:46,080 --> 00:46:49,360
When Earn arrives,
maybe she should sit here?

560
00:46:49,360 --> 00:46:50,920
Eh? Where are you going?

561
00:46:50,920 --> 00:46:52,000
A different bar.

562
00:46:52,400 --> 00:46:54,520
Goodness, she's wasted.

563
00:46:54,520 --> 00:46:56,440
-Plus she's alone.
-Suzie?

564
00:46:56,920 --> 00:46:58,040
I'll take care of her.

565
00:46:58,160 --> 00:47:00,400
Doc, why did you get so drunk?

566
00:47:16,000 --> 00:47:20,440
♪ Please don't let go of my hand ♪

567
00:47:22,080 --> 00:47:26,880
♪ No matter what, please be right here ♪

568
00:47:28,080 --> 00:47:31,200
♪ Having you here is reassuring ♪

569
00:47:31,200 --> 00:47:34,600
♪ I'm less anxious than I used to be ♪

570
00:47:35,640 --> 00:47:42,320
 ♪ You're the good love I never experienced ♪
